text: Los Angeles County’s temporary stay at home order bans all private and public gatherings with people from more than one household, except for faith-based services and protests, said Dr. Barbara Ferrer, the county’s public health director. https://t.co/9Lu9uBAUks

name: sfchronicle
text:
The changes come amid record-setting highs for single-day case counts and coronavirus-related hospitalizations since the start of the pandemic. 

As of Saturday, there were 760 new cases and 239 hospitalizations in the county. https://t.co/vdxGvEo0Nn

name: sfchronicle
text:
Stanford and San Jose State’s football and basketball teams will not be able to play or practice at home for the next several weeks under a revised health order issued by Santa Clara County public health officials.

https://t.co/PRRWPyGNl7

name: sfchronicle
text: Many restaurants in the Bay Area can offer only outdoor dining because of coronavirus restrictions. With temperatures dropping, restaurants are looking frantically for heat lamps — and having trouble finding them. https://t.co/iyik9PlINj

name: sfchronicle
text:
Coronavirus cases in San Francisco have tripled over the past four weeks, public health officials said.

The city has reported an average of 130 new cases a day this week, compared to 73 per day in the first week of November. https://t.co/5B4KhzK1Nb https://t.co/mz8gWq6Kt2

name: sfchronicle
text:
JUST IN: The nine Bay Area counties together reported 2,027 new coronavirus cases by Saturday afternoon — a new daily high for the region, according to data reported by county health departments and compiled by The Chronicle and the L.A. Times.

https://t.co/tG7r9uCI4C

text: Janet Yellen, President-elect Joe Biden’s expected nominee for Treasury secretary, would be the first woman to lead the department if confirmed, after breaking barriers as the first woman to chair the Federal Reserve from 2014 to 2018. https://t.co/e22QswvG4l
